Sample Rexx Programs

Assumptions for all of the programs

  o EZSUBADR (alias EZSUBCOM) and GETCERTS are in the program object
    (load) library named in the statement
    LOADLIB = 'MY.LOAD'
  o Running under TSO or TSO batch
  o User has RACF permissions as indicated for each function


GETCERTS     Rexx Certificate Library for RACF   Page 17



Sample 1     List all certificate expiration dates Lists all
certificates with their expiration dates.

/* Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS showing all expiration
   dates */

Say "Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS by showing all",
    "expiration dates"

LOADLIB = 'MY.LOAD'

If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB DATASET ID("LOADLIB") STACK"
  End              /* SYSISPF */

ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(GCPRINT) SYSOUT"
ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(MYLOADDD) DA("LOADLIB") SHR"

/* Use EZSUBCOM to load GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'ADDLESUB', 'GETCERTS',,, 'MYLOADDD'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode < 0 | ReturnCode > 4 Then Do
  Say "Return Code" ReturnCode "from EZSUBCOM ADDLESUB GETCERTS"
  Signal Sig_EndPgm
  End  /* Bad RC from EZSUBCOM */

/* Get basic certificate information */
ADDRESS GETCERTS 'CERTSUMM'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode > 0 Then Say "RESULT =" RESULT
If ReturnCode > 8 Then Signal Sig_EndPgm

/* For each certificate say the expiration date */
Do i = 1 to CERTUSER.0
  Say NOTAFTER.i CERTUSER.i LABEL.i SUBJECT$.i
  End i

/* Unload GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'DELETE', 'GETCERTS'

/* End of Rexx EXEC */
Sig_EndPgm:
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(GCPRINT)"
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(MYLOADDD)"
If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB"
  End              /* SYSISPF */
Exit 0

GETCERTS     Rexx Certificate Library for RACF   Page 18



Sample 2     List all empty keyrings Lists all keyrings that contain
no certificates.

/* Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS by showing all empty
   keyrings */

Say "Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS by showing all",
    "empty keyrings"

LOADLIB = 'MY.LOAD'

If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB DATASET ID("LOADLIB") STACK"
  End              /* SYSISPF */

ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(GCPRINT) SYSOUT"
ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(MYLOADDD) DA("LOADLIB") SHR"

/* Use EZSUBCOM to load GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'ADDLESUB', 'GETCERTS',,, 'MYLOADDD'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode < 0 | ReturnCode > 4 Then Do
  Say "Return Code" ReturnCode "from EZSUBCOM ADDLESUB GETCERTS"
  Signal Sig_EndPgm
  End  /* Bad RC from EZSUBCOM */

/* Get basic certificate information */
ADDRESS GETCERTS 'CERTSUMM'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode > 0 Then Say "RESULT =" RESULT
If ReturnCode > 8 Then Signal Sig_EndPgm

/* Get keyring information */
ADDRESS GETCERTS 'RINGSUMM'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode > 0 Then Say "RESULT =" RESULT
If ReturnCode > 8 Then Signal Sig_EndPgm

/* List each empty keyring */
Do i = 1 to NAME.0
  If CONCERT#.i = '' Then Say RINGUSER.i NAME.i
  End i

/* Unload GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'DELETE', 'GETCERTS'

/* End of Rexx EXEC */
Sig_EndPgm:
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(GCPRINT)"
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(MYLOADDD)"
If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB"
  End              /* SYSISPF */
Exit 0

GETCERTS     Rexx Certificate Library for RACF   Page 19



Sample 3     List all keyrings with no unexpired, trusted certificates
Lists all keyrings that contain no unexpired, trusted certificates.
Lists the owner, the first 20 characters of the ring name and the
userid that defined the keyring, with the date that they defined it.
Sample output:

Owner    Name                 Who Added and When
-------- -------------------- -------- ----------
ABSMITH  Smith.Ring           FRIKDJ   2026-01-25
FRED     fred.testring        FRED     2025-07-03
IBMCERT  IBMInternetServiceRe IBUSER1  2010-09-21
TN3270   TN3270RING           IBUSER1  2011-09-06


/* Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS by showing unusable
   keyrings */

Say "Rexx program to demonstrate GETCERTS by showing all keyrings",
    "with no unexpired certificates"

LOADLIB = 'MY.LOAD'

If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB DATASET ID("LOADLIB") STACK"
  End              /* SYSISPF */

ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(GCPRINT) SYSOUT"
ADDRESS TSO "ALLOC FI(MYLOADDD) DA("LOADLIB") SHR"

/* Set up a comparison time in ISO 8601 format 2025-12-19T00:00:00 */
DateNow = DATE('S'); TimeNow = TIME('N')
Now = Left(DateNow,4) || "-" || Substr(DateNow,5,2) || "-" ||,
      Right(DateNow,2)
Now = Now || "T" || TimeNow

/* Use EZSUBCOM to load GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'ADDLESUB', 'GETCERTS',,, 'MYLOADDD'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode < 0 | ReturnCode > 4 Then Do
  Say "Return Code" ReturnCode "from EZSUBCOM ADDLESUB GETCERTS"
  Signal Sig_EndPgm
  End  /* Bad RC from EZSUBCOM */

/* Get basic certificate information */
ADDRESS GETCERTS 'CERTSUMM'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode > 0 Then Say "RESULT =" RESULT
If ReturnCode > 8 Then Signal Sig_EndPgm

/* Get keyring information */
ADDRESS GETCERTS 'RINGSUMM'
ReturnCode = RC
If ReturnCode > 0 Then Say "RESULT =" RESULT
If ReturnCode > 8 Then Signal Sig_EndPgm


GETCERTS     Rexx Certificate Library for RACF   Page 20



/* For each keyring, check expiration & trust of each connected
certificate */

Say "Owner    Name                 Who Added and When"
Say "-------- -------------------- -------- ----------"
Do k = 1 to NAME.0
  IsUseful = 0
  Do w = 1 to Words(CONCERT#.k)
    c = Word(CONCERT#.k, w)
    If NOTAFTER.c > Now Then Do
      IsUseful = 1
      Leave
      End
    End w
  If \ IsUseful Then Do
   Say Left(RINGUSER.k,8) Left(NAME.k,20) Left(RINGUADD.k,8),
       Left(RINGDADD.k,10)
   End
  End k

/* Unload GETCERTS */
Call 'EZSUBCOM' 'DELETE', 'GETCERTS'
/* End of Rexx EXEC */

Sig_EndPgm:
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(GCPRINT)"
ADDRESS TSO "FREE FI(MYLOADDD)"
If Sysvar("SYSISPF") = "ACTIVE" Then Do
  ADDRESS ISPEXEC "LIBDEF ISPLLIB"
  End              /* SYSISPF */
Exit 0

GETCERTS     Rexx Certificate Library for RACF   Page 21
